## XII. CONCLUSION & STRATEGIC SUMMARY

### The Parrot Turnaround: From Consumer Darling to Defense Powerhouse

**2010–2015:** Consumer drone pioneer. Market leader. Valuation peak.

**2016–2017:** Industry shakeout. Consumer drone bubble collapse. Parrot ruthlessly restructured (–35% headcount). Exited consumer electronics. Survived where competitors (3DR, Lily, GoPro) failed.

**2017–2023:** Slow pivot to professional/defense markets. ANAFI USA launched. U.S. DoD foothold established. Pix4D integration deepened. But profitability elusive. Accumulated losses €50M+. Stock price depressed.

**2024–2025:** **Inflection year.** Revenue growth resumed (20% 2024, 17% H1 2025). Operating leverage emerging. ANAFI UKR launched. European defense contracts flowing. H2 2024 achieved operating profitability. Trajectory clearly toward sustained profitability.

**2025–2027:** **Growth phase.** European defense budget relaunch fueling demand. ANAFI UKR product line expanding. U.S. market penetration accelerating. Pix4D SaaS scaling. Manufacturing optimization underway. Distribution network expanding.

